  "messages": [
    {
      "id": "5c57b69f4d0eaf131d0be7380bd7cd7df4d1d91c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-14 06:06:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nI'd actually be happier with returning -EREMOTE to old clients, since this is more clear about what the reason for the error is instead of actually having an IO error or eviction or some other similar error.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d0b4bb6bc0dec3ea88b1fc5e89c1f362d052c349",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-14 06:48:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIf we return EREMOTE to the old client, it will still try to access another MDT in LMV, instead of returning to the application directly, which might cause some unexpected consequence here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d93fae1d191a07899ac47835fafa5c876c03bfb4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-15 03:36:44.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 2.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "9489b3065f38a0302a31e1aba2a7a208c0ebd211",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-15 04:03:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nHmm, maybe I'm not understanding, but won't old clients not understand -EREMOTE?  Or is -EREMOTE available in 2.x because of CMD, but they won't do the right thing?  I thought -EREMOTE was new with DNE1.  When you wrote \"old client\" I was thinking \"1.8\", not \"2.1\".",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "8416b07b8233fb090ab906deca5151a1f7bd3373",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-15 04:41:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nyes, 2.x(1,2,3) client also understands -EREMOTE because of CMD, but it may try to do sth wrong. Though I did not test that.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
